Name: Security Level Code
Notes: Code indicating the level of confidentiality assigned by the sender to the information following

Name: Security Technique Code
Notes: Code indicating that this element will be used to tell an EDI translator program which security technique to use

Name: Version Identifier
Notes: Revision level of a particular format, program, technique or algorithm

Name: Program Identifier
Notes: Identifies the name of the software program from which the technical data originates
Remarks: C0504: If EFI-05 is present, then EFI-04 is required

Name: Version Identifier
Notes: Revision level of a particular format, program, technique or algorithm

Name: Interchange Format
Notes: Industry or proprietary standard used to identify the format of the data
Remarks: C0706: If EFI-07 is present, then EFI-06 is required

Name: Version Identifier
Notes: Revision level of a particular format, program, technique or algorithm

Name: Compression Technique
Notes: Identifies the digital data compression means and the type
Remarks: C0908: If EFI-09 is present, then EFI-08 is required

Name: Drawing Sheet Size Code
Notes: Code indicating the drawing size and orientation of a technical drawing as specified and described in the current version of standards ANSI Y14.1 and ISO 5457 (E); see the listed ANSI and ISO standards for the maximum lengths for rolled sheets *

Name: File Name
Notes: Name assigned or declared for a file or used by a program to identify a file; exact format of the name depends on the computer operating system being used; name also may be known as the file's "data set name"

Name: Block Type
Notes: Organization of a data block such as fixed length, variable length, spanned, etc. Synonym for "data format"

Name: Record Length
Notes: Quantity of characters or bytes in a record. Synonyms are "logical record length" and "record size"

Name: Block Length
Notes: Quantity of data elements in a block, usually specified in units such as records, words or characters; synonym for "block size"

Name: Version Identifier
Notes: Revision level of a particular format, program, technique or algorithm
Remarks: P1516: If either EFI-15 or EFI-16 is present, then the other is required

Name: Filter ID Code
Notes: Code specifying the type of filter used to convert data code values
